    <div class="container">
      <div class="row block block-hero block-centered">
        <article class="col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2">
          <h1>Business Continuity Specialist</h1>
          
            <p>Business Continuity Specialists provide crucial operational support and guidance to the safety of a global organization and aid in the development and implementation of innovative new corporate safety programs. (If you immediately know what that sentence means: Congratulations! You’re home.)</p>

          

          <a href="#view-open-positions" class="button button-white button-hover-white">View Openings for this Role</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div><!-- /.container -->
  </div><!-- /#hero-wrapper-auto -->

<!-- career-role-template body -->

<div class="container section">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="job-description col-md-6">
      <h2>A World-Changing Company</h2>
      <p>At Palantir, we develop the world's leading products for data analysis and we deploy them against problems that truly matter—uncovering human trafficking rings, containing the spread of infectious diseases, combating fraud, stopping cyber attacks, protecting privacy and civil liberties, prosecuting complex financial crimes, providing relief to victims of natural disasters, and more.</p>
      <h2>The role</h2>
      
        <p>There is a line that separates a safe, supportive environment from a dangerous, closed environment. Palantir Security holds that line. Our goal as a team: provide and maintain a comfortable, open workplace without sacrificing our culture or safety. We have engineers, analysts and people who do a bit of everything; we lean heavily on that diversity of skill to address a wide array of challenges with as deft a touch as possible. In a nutshell, when you do things right, people won’t be sure you’ve done anything at all.</p>

        
          <h2 id="responsibilities">Responsibilities</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Develop and implement corporate safety policies and training programs, lead initiatives to reduce work process risk, and raise safety awareness</li>
  <li>Responsible for the management of Palantir’s business continuity life cycle and strategy, including assessments, communication, documentation, and testing</li>
  <li>Execute company safety policies and ensure compliance to all applicable local and regional regulations</li>
  <li>Perform frequent site safety audits to identify all non-compliance equipment and/or processes to ensure we’re providing a safe environment for all employees and associates</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="requirements">Requirements</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Well organized with a proven ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment</li>
  <li>Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills</li>
  <li>Strong analytical skills with demonstrated problem solving ability</li>
  <li>Must be willing to travel</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="preferred">Preferred</h2>

<ul>
  <li>3-5 years of related work experience</li>
  <li>Industry certifications are a plus (CBCP, CSP, or CEM)</li>
  <li>BA/BS degree or equivalent practical experience</li>
</ul>

        
      
    </div>
    <div class="resources col-md-offset-2 col-md-4">
      <h2>Resources</h2>

      <div class="clearfix">
        

        

        <div class="resources-item">
          <h3><a href= "/careers/teams/security" title="Security">Security</a></h3>
          <p>We are engineers, analysts, and operators who do just a little bit of everything. We hold the line that separates a safe, supportive environment from a dangerous, closed environment.
</p>
        </div>

        <div class="resources-item">
          <h3><a href="/engineering-culture/" title="">Engineering Culture</a></h3>
          <p>Engineers build things that solve problems, but at Palantir you don't have to be a computer scientist to be an engineer. You do have to speak up when things aren't right and build things that fix what's broken.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="resources-item">
          <h3><a href="/life-at-palantir/" title="">Life at Palantir</a></h3>
          <p>Perks, benefits, social activities, and learning opportunities: people are our most important asset, so we invest in our people every day.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="resources-item">
          <h3><a href="/getting-hired/" title="">Getting Hired</a></h3>
          <p>If you want to stare into the face of important problems and have the freedom to solve them, we want to work with you. We have some resources to help you navigate the hiring process.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

